  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The two factors that prevent cheesecake cracking are the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "bain-marie"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "bain-marie (water bath)"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and leaving the cake to cool slowly in the oven with the door ajar. Cracking comes from rapid temperature change, not from any error in the batter. The sour cream topping is partially practical: it masks any surface crack that does appear, and adds a clean, tangy note that cuts the richness of the filling."
          }
        ]
      },
